@startuml error-propagation
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica"
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #333333
skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #F5F5F5
skinparam ParticipantBorderColor #888888
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFFFCC
skinparam NoteBorderColor #CCCC88
skinparam SequenceGroupBackgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam SequenceGroupBorderColor #AAAAAA

title Propagation d'erreurs dans un systeme multi-agent\nRecovery locale puis propagation structuree

participant "Coordinateur\n(Orchestrator)" as coord #BBDEFB
participant "Subagent A\n(Writer 1)" as agentA #80CBC4
participant "Subagent B\n(Writer 2)" as agentB #80CBC4
participant "Subagent C\n(Writer 3)" as agentC #80CBC4

== Execution parallele ==

coord -> agentA : Tache slide 1
coord -> agentB : Tache slide 2
coord -> agentC : Tache slide 3

agentA --> coord : SlideContent OK
note right of agentA : Succes

agentB --> agentB : Erreur API transitoire
note right of agentB
  **Recovery locale**
  Retry automatique
  (erreur transitoire)
end note
agentB --> coord : SlideContent OK\n(apres retry)

agentC --> agentC : Erreur persistante
note right of agentC #FFEBEE
  **Echec apres retries**
  Erreur non resolvable
  localement
end note
agentC --> coord : **Erreur structuree**\nfmt.Errorf("writer slide 3: %w", err)

== Aggregation des resultats ==

note over coord
  **Aggregation** (orchestrator.go:294-296)
  ----
  Resultats partiels : slides 1, 2 OK
  Erreurs : errors.Join(writerErrors...)
  ----
  **Decision** : continuer avec resultats partiels
  ou propager l'erreur ?
end note

alt Tous les agents reussissent
  coord -> coord : Continuer le pipeline
else Echecs partiels
  coord -> coord : Evaluer l'impact
  note right of coord
    **Anti-patterns a eviter**
    ----
    X Masquer l'erreur (return success)
    X Abandonner tout le pipeline
    X Message generique "erreur"
    ----
    **Bonne pratique** :
    Propager le contexte complet
    (type, tentative, resultats partiels)
  end note
end

@enduml
